  "name": "Crimson Brand",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>These ominous swords are decorated with crimson lacquer and serve as perfect conduits for the Crimson Oath's power. The first was granted to Clarethe Iomedar by a mysterious patron who many Reclaimers believe to be an emissary of Ragathiel.</p>\n<p>A crimson brand is a +1 striking @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.fo6Yhq5mbQXsnZs0]{Wounding} bastard sword. When the wielder uses the crimson brand to cast <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.AsKLseOo8hwv5Jha]{Invoke the Crimson Oath}</em>, they can generate a @Template[type:line|distance:60] or a @Template[type:cone|distance:30] instead of the normal @Template[type:cone|distance:20].</p>\n<p>Whenever the wielder would inflict persistent bleed damage on an undead creature with the <em>crimson brand</em>, they can instead wreathe the creature in ruby energy, inflicting the same amount of persistent positive damage instead of persistent bleed damage.</p>"
    },
